cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper is about object detection using convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which is a popular topic in computer vision (CV) research. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new training method that involves adjusting the learning rate and using Cross-GPU Batch Normalization, which are related to machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.LG and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of multiple GPUs, which is related to parallel computing and neural networks (NE), making cs.NE a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the results of their approach on the COCO dataset, which is a benchmark for object detection and segmentation, making cs.MM a possible sub-category as well.
